![2, ten dollar bills. 1, five dollar bill. 3, one dollar bills.](https://cdn.kastatic.org/ka-perseus-images/4eb2752b7d969eb1c04022bd77339f0047021006.png)

$\begin{align}
&\underbrace{\$\goldE{10}+\$\goldE{10}}_{\goldE{2}{\text{ ten dollar bills}}}  
 + \underbrace{\$\purpleD{5}}_{\purpleD{1}{\text{ five dollar bill}}}   +\underbrace{\$\blueE{1}+\$\blueE{1} + \$\blueE{1}}_{\blueE{3}{\text{ one dollar bills}}}\\\\
&\underbrace{\$\goldE{20}}_{\goldE{2}{\text{ ten dollar bills}}}  
 + \underbrace{\$\purpleD{5}}_{\purpleD{1}{\text{ five dollar bill}}}   +\underbrace{\$\blueE{3}}_{\blueE{3}{\text{ one dollar bills}}}=\$28
\end{align}$

This set of bills has a value of $\$28$, so it is **not** equal to $\$29$.

![1, ten dollar bill. 1, five dollar bill. 4, one dollar bills.](https://cdn.kastatic.org/ka-perseus-images/0354c9ba52dc61658ccf6709af31a30be1394b0b.png)

$\begin{align}
&\underbrace{\$\goldE{10}}_{\goldE{1}{\text{ ten dollar bill}}}  
 + \underbrace{\$\purpleD{5}}_{\purpleD{1}{\text{ five dollar bill}}}   +\underbrace{\$\blueE{1}+\$\blueE{1} + \$\blueE{1} + \$\blueE{1}}_{\blueE{4}{\text{ one dollar bills}}}\\\\
&\underbrace{\$\goldE{10}}_{\goldE{1}{\text{ ten dollar bill}}}  
 + \underbrace{\$\purpleD{5}}_{\purpleD{1}{\text{ five dollar bill}}}   +\underbrace{\$\blueE{4}}_{\blueE{4}{\text{ one dollar bills}}}=\$19
\end{align}$

This set of bills has a value of $\$19$, so it is **not** equal to $\$29$.
